      END-OF-FILE POINTER
           A pointer to the  actual end of data in the  file, i.e., the
      pointer to where the next CUD change record will be stored.
-     LAST CLASS/GROUP CREATION TIME
           The ISIS time of the last SEND command.
-     CONSISTENCY START TIME
           The time,  in minutes  since midnight, of  the start  of the
      automatic consistency period.
-     CONSISTENCY STOP TIME
           The time, in minutes since midnight, of the end of the auto-
      matic consistency period.
-     LAST RECORD POINTER
           A pointer to  the beginning of the last record  in the file;
      used to recover  appropriately from a crash during  a pending MUD
      change notification.
-     LAST MERGE TIME
           If  Reuse  Uuns  are  enabled   in  the  configuraiton  file
      (NVAL##.A##), this  is the time  of the  last merge of  the added
      back UUNs.
-     For each possible Supervisor (121-127):
           FLAG
                The value 0  - 7; if zero, the Supervisor  has not been
           turned ON  by the SET  command, otherwise, 1  for Supervisor
           121, 2 for Supervisor 122, etc.
